      <hedline>
        <hl1>Musical Innovators</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Edward Goodstein letter on Terry Teachout's April 30 article on Dave's True Story holds Dave Cantor may be only songwriter today who is able to emulate Lou Reed and Johnny Mercer0</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I very much appreciated Terry Teachout's informative and insightful article about Dave's True Story [''A Little Disturbing, A Little Unnerving: Postmodern Lounge,'' April 30]. I think they are among the most innovative music groups of the last few years, showing that Hollywood flash and painful decibel levels are not required for pop music creativity. Dave Cantor (pace to his mentor, Walter Fagen) may be the only songwriter today who has been able to forge lyrics that evoke both Lou Reed and Johnny Mercer.</p>
        <p>EDWARD GOODSTEIN  Atherton, Calif.</p>
      </block>
